backgoundStudy: The former President of Somalia (2017–2022), has an academic background in history and political science. He studied in the United States, earning a Bachelor’s degree in Political Science from the University at Buffalo, New York. His studies focused on governance, public administration, and political systems, which later influenced his political career.

The former Prime Minister of Somalia (2017–2020), has an academic background in management and business administration. He studied in Norway and earned a Bachelor’s degree in Political Science and a Master’s degree in Business Administration (MBA) from Heriot-Watt University in Scotland.

The current President of Puntland (since 2019) and a Somali politician, has an academic background in business and economics. He studied in Sudan, where he earned a degree in Business Administration and Economics.
